the EHRC report finds the Labour party acted unlawfully

the Anti-Semitism issue goes beyond just Jeremy Corbyn
Keir Starmer has questions to answer himself

Kier Starmer didn’t resign from Jeremy Corbyn's front bench
Kier Starmer defended Jeremy Corbyn, and indeed he promoted Jeremy Corbyn as a potential Prime Minister less than a year ago
Keir Starmer needs to do two things if he’s serious about fixing this
Kier Starmer should apologise personally for his failure to speak out on this issue when he was on the front bench
it was all very convenient for Kier Starmer to sit there and say quiet in the hope that he would then take over as leader

the EHRC report is so damning
Jeremy Corbyn’s response to the EHRC report this morning saying the whole thing had been hugely exaggerated for political purposes, was disgraceful
Kier Starmer needs to do those two things- apologise and remove Jeremy Corbyn- if he’s really serious about fixing this issue
